value: Resident and visitor, open savannas:  all S of Sahara except forest area and parts of NE and SW; breeding visitor Senegal - Ethiopia and south of N Angola - C Tanzania; resident around L. Victoria; movements not clear (jacobinus breeds India, winters E and C Africa, serratus in South Africa, pica in rest of range).
Africa, Asia: widespread in AF, India to Myanmar

subcat_descr: Bill length (sex unknown) - Nares to tip

value: males and females share resources on their territory only during the breeding season
